rn new Response(stream, { status: 200, headers: { 'content-type': 'text/event-stream' } });\n}\n```\n\nFake fetch:\n```ts\nfunction makeFakeFetch(chunks: string[], capture?: (req: Request) => void): typeof fetch {\n  return async (input: RequestInfo | URL, init?: RequestInit) => {\n    const req = new Request(input, init);\n    if (capture) capture(req);\n    return makeSseResponse(chunks);\n  };\n}\n```\n\nWait, `typeof fetch` signature. In TS lib, `fetch` is `(input: string | Request | URL, init?: RequestInit) => Promise<Response>`. Let me type fetchImpl as `typeof fetch`.\n\nFor capturing request body: `const body = await req.text()` then JSON.parse.\n\nLet me write tests:\n\n1. OpenAI text streaming: canned SSE with a few text chunks, usage, [DONE]. Assert events.\n2. OpenAI tool call: canned SSE with tool_calls deltas, [DONE]. Assert tool-call-delta then tool-call with parsed args, stopReason 'tool_use'.\n3. Missing key: empty env → single error event.\n4. Abort: pre-aborted signal → aborted event, no throw.\n5. OpenRouter no-train: capture request body, assert provider.data_collection === 'deny', no 'only' field.\n6. No event contains the API key.\n\nLet me write canned SSE for OpenAI text:\n\n```\ndata: {\"choices\":[{\"delta\":{\"content\":\"Hello\"}}]}\n\ndata: {\"choices\":[{\"delta\":{\"content\":\" world\"}}]}\n\ndata: {\"choices\":[{\"delta\":{},\"finish_reason\":\"stop\"}],\"usage\":{\"prompt_tokens\":5,\"completion_tokens\":2}}\n\ndata: [DONE]\n\n```\n\nNote: SSE events separated by blank lines. Each `data:` line.\n\nFor tool call:\n```\ndata: {\"choices\":[{\"delta\":{\"tool_calls\":[{\"index\":0,\"id\":\"call_1\",\"function\":{\"name\":\"get_weather\",\"arguments\":\"\"}}]}}]}\n\ndata: {\"choices\":[{\"delta\":{\"tool_calls\":[{\"index\":0,\"function\":{\"arguments\":\"{\\\"city\\\":\"}}]}}]}\n\ndata: {\"choices\":[{\"delta\":{\"tool_calls\":[{\"index\":0,\"function\":{\"arguments\":\"\\\"SF\\\"}\"}}]}}]}\n\ndata: {\"choices\":[{\"delta\":{},\"finis